@database "Object manager Guide"
@author "Heiko Schr—der"
@$VER: 3.0 (Release 3)
@wordwrap

@node Main "Object Manager V1.0"
                               @{" < Table of Contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

         !!! This Macro only works with £Final Writer 97¨ !!!

@{fg shine}Benifits:@{fg text}
   The search for objects in a large document finally has an end.
   With this macro you can easily find any object in any section of your
   document, alter its properties, and delete it.

@{fg shine}Requirements:@{fg text}
   £Final Writer 97¨ or later
   Documents with Objects ;-)

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview ObjectManager.iff"}:@{fg text}

      When the Macro starts it will search for all of the objects in the
      document. Then it will list the section name, the Page, the Object
      number (ID), the type of all the objects.

      @{fg fill}S@{fg text}ections
         If there are too many objects in the list you can select just one
         section to view the objects of.
         
      @{fg fill}A@{fg text}ll
         The macro will list all objects in the document.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

      Sho@{fg fill}w@{fg text}
         The object currently selected on the list will be displayed on the 
         screen.

      @{fg fill}P@{fg text}roperties
         This will open the standard Final Writer object preferences window.
         Warning: This will not work with grouped objects. If a group is
                  selected this button will be ghosted.

      @{fg fill}D@{fg text}elete
         Will delete the object currently selected in the list.

      @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or closing the window
         Terminates the Macro.

@{fg shine}Hint:@{fg text}
      The format of the List uses the "rexxreqtools.library"
      The macro is otherwise completly working.
@endnode
